        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 25 at 5:01PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 501 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was near Conasauga Lake, or 11
miles east of Chatsworth. This storm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, up to penny sized hail and frequent
cloud to ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Crandall, Conasauga Lake, and Jones Mill.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
